RCMP reported the apprehension at Toronto Airport on 1 November, 2003 of a man posing as a Dominican priest. This man was traveling from CDG, Paris on a French passport under the name: Fr. Augustin Dominique, having the address 174 Rue Cardinet, Paris. When asked a question about his destination in Toronto, the man mistakenly answered in Arabic rather than in French. CSIS have identified this man as Abdal al Hawsawi, a Saudi now known to have been associated with a chemical weapons expert in Afghanistan named Abdul Ahmed Nasser. On the ticket folder Hawsawi was carrying appeared the address: 1712 Ferry St, Buffalo, NY..
